1.1 PA Measurement Reactivity R03 Background

Contact Info

Principal Investigator: Danielle Arigo, Ph.D.1

Background and Funding

Grant Title: Predictors of Reactivity to Physical Activity Measurement among Women in Midlife with Elevated CVD Risk: Examination Across 7 Studies

Risk for cardiovascular disease (CVD) substantially increases during midlife (ages 40-60) and risk trajectories differ for women and men. Increasing physical activity (PA) can mitigate these risks and there is a critical need for research that can reduce barriers to engagement in this population. PA measurement reactivity, or a change in PA engagement in response to the introduction of PA measurement, may bias the objective assessment of PA that is essential to evaluating PA promotion efforts. At present, however, evidence supporting PA measurement reactivity as a key confound in PA research is mixed, including preliminary evidence from the investigative team. Our funded R03 is designed to address key limitations of existing work â including emphasis on children or healthy, young adults with low risk for CVD and lack of attention to individual differences between participants â among women in midlife with elevated CVD risk (e.g., obesity, hypertension; N = 800). The proposed supplement is designed to further address limitations of low power for conducting critical tests of gender differences in PA measurement reactivity responses, by including men and conducting the first fully powered test of gender differences in this area. We will use 6 existing datasets from NIH-funded clinical trials and publicly available databases to examine gender differences in PA measurement reactivity among midlife adults with elevated CVD risk (N = 1940). Using a coordinated analysis approach, we will employ multilevel modeling techniques to achieve the following aims: (1) To characterize midlife adultsâ PA measurement reactivity across 4 PA outcomes (full sample and within genders): steps, minutes of light activity, minutes of moderate-to-vigorous intensity activity, and minutes of sedentary behavior, (2) To determine whether the presence or extent of measurement reactivity differ based on demographic, medical, or psychological characteristics (with emphasis on gender), and (3) To determine whether the presence or extent of measurement reactivity differ based on study characteristics such as research design (i.e., observation only vs.Â PA observation prior to the start of an intervention) and PA monitoring procedures (i.e., research-grade accelerometers vs.Â commercially available wearables). We will also examine whether gender moderates the influence of characteristics such as study design, BMI, or depressive symptoms. This work will identify circumstances associated with problematic levels of PA measurement reactivity among adults in midlife and potential gender-specific targets for reducing it in an at-risk group. This R03 supplement thus represents an important extension of funded work that leverages existing data sources to increase the scientific rigor of research in the fields of PA measurement and intervention, and to provide high-quality evidence that speaks to potential gender differences in PA measurement reactivity responses. â NIH Reporter (#3R03HL160602-02S1)

1.2 MIDUS Background

The first national survey of Midlife Development in the U.S. (MIDUS) was conducted in 1995/96 by the MacArthur Foundation Research Network on Successful Midlife Development. The study was conceived by a multidisciplinary team of scholars from fields of psychology, sociology, epidemiology, demography, anthropology, medicine, and health care policy. Their collective aim was to investigate the role of behavioral, psychological, and social factors in accounting for age-related variations in health and well-being in a national sample of Americans. In addition to a national probability sample (N = 3,487), the study included over-samples in select metropolitan areas (N = 757), a sample of siblings (N = 950) of the main respondents, and a national sample of twin pairs (N=1,914).

The first wave of data collection â¦ consisted of a general population survey, as well as surveys of siblings of the general population respondents, and a twin pairs sample. The main data collection also included an oversample of five metropolitan areas. In addition to the main national survey, random subsamples of respondents were recruited to participate in in-depth investigations of selected topics, such as management strategies for coping with stressful experiences, a national study of daily experiences, and a study of psychological experiences.

In 2002 the University of Wisconsin Institute on Aging was awarded a grant from the National Institute on Aging to continue the MIDUS series.

In 2011-2014, the MIDUS Refresher study recruited a national probability sample of 3,577 adults, aged 25 to 74, designed to replenish the original MIDUS 1 baseline cohort and paralleling the five decadal age groups of the MIDUS 1 baseline survey. The MIDUS Refresher survey employed the same comprehensive assessments as those assembled on the existing MIDUS sample, but with additional questions about the effect of the economic recession of 2008-09. This new cross-sectional MIDUS sample allows the examination of period effects on health (mental and physical) related to the economic recession by comparing the pre-recession MIDUS 1 sample with the post-recession MIDUS Refresher sample.

â Modified excerpts from https://midus.wisc.edu/

3 Updating Core Exclusion Flag

data_all_pers <- data_all_pers %>%
  mutate(
    core_excl2 = case_when(
      is.na(age_num) | is.na(gender_num) | is.na(pre_CVD) | is.na(CVD_risk_sum) ~ 1,
      age_40_to_60_num == 1 & pre_CVD == 0 & CVD_risk_sum >= 1 ~ 0,
      TRUE ~ 1
    ),
    core_excl2 = sjlabelled::set_labels(
      core_excl2,
      labels = c(
        `0` = "Include participant",
        `1` = "Exclude participant"
      ),
      force.labels = TRUE,
      force.values = TRUE,
    ),
    core_excl2 = datawizard::assign_labels(
      core_excl2,
      variable = "bin flag: whether a person should be included (0) or excluded (1) based on core exclusion criteria (updated to exclude those without 1+ risk factors or not enough info)"
    ),
    core_excl2_fct = sjlabelled::as_label(core_excl2,
      add.non.labelled = TRUE,
      prefix = TRUE
    )
  )

CB_all <- CB_add_OG(CB_all, data_all_pers, (data_all_pers %>% select(contains("core")) %>% colnames()), vlabel = TRUE)

data_all_pers <- reapply_attr2(CB_all, data_all_pers)
data_all_pers %>%
  mutate(
    CVD_risk_sum = case_when(
      is.na(CVD_risk_sum) ~ 0,
      CVD_risk_sum >= 1 ~ 1,
      CVD_risk_sum < 1 ~ 0,
      TRUE ~ 9999
    )
  ) %>%
  count(core_excl2_fct, age_40_to_60_fct, pre_CVD_fct, CVD_risk_sum) %>%
  select(n, everything()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  def_reactable(
    defminWidth = 100,
    firstminWidth = 50
  )
data_all_pers %>%
  count(core_excl_fct, core_excl2_fct) %>%
  select(n, everything()) %>%
  arrange(desc(n)) %>%
  def_reactable(
    defminWidth = 100,
    firstminWidth = 50
  )

4 Physical Activity Variables

The actigraphy-derived PA data in MIDUS is part of the P4 sleep data. It appears the investigators were most focused on actigraphy related to sleep, but day-time actigraphy data is also available. Participants kept daily sleep diaries, which were used to understand and clean the actigraphy data.

This data was collected starting the âTuesday after the day the respondent returns home following the GCRC visit.â There are a total of 7 rest periods, 7 sleep periods, and 6 active periods. These different periods were defined using information from the sleep diary.

  • Rest: Time spent in bed trying to sleep (based on sleep diary self-reports)
  • Sleep/Wake: Automatically scored by Actiware software

The most detailed information appears in M2P4 Sleep Data Documentation.

We will be using the actigraphy data from the âactiveâ periods.

4.4 Converting PA to Long-Format

Converting all actigraphy variables to long format

data_PA <- data_all_pers %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = matches("^M2P4_1_B4W[ARS]\\d+[A-Za-z0-9_.]+$"),
    names_to = c("prefix", "PA_data_day", "suffix"),
    names_pattern = "^M2P4_1_(B4W[ARS])(\\d+)([A-Za-z0-9_.]+)$",
    values_drop_na = TRUE
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    PA_data_day = as.integer(PA_data_day)
  ) %>%
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = c(prefix, suffix),
    values_from = value,
    names_sep = "_"
  )

# List of suffix explanations
suffix_explanations <- list(
  SDY = "start day",
  ST = "start time",
  EDY = "end day",
  ET = "end time",
  TAC = "total activity counts",
  ACM = "average activity counts/min",
  MAC = "maximum activity counts",
  IAC = "invalid activity counts",
  SW = "percent invalid sleep/wake time",
  WT = "wake time",
  PW = "percent wake time",
  WB = "wake bouts",
  AWB = "average wake bouts",
  SLT = "sleep time",
  PSL = "percent sleep time",
  SLB = "sleep bouts",
  ASB = "average sleep bouts",
  ISW = "percent invalid sleep/wake time",
  OL = "sleep onset latency",
  SNT = "time dozing before rising",
  EFF = "sleep efficiency",
  WSO = "wake after sleep onset"
)

# Function to assign labels based on the suffix explanations
assign_variable_labels <- function(data, prefixes, suffix_explanations) {
  for (prefix in prefixes) {
    for (suffix in names(suffix_explanations)) {
      var_name <- paste0(prefix, "_", suffix)
      if (var_name %in% colnames(data)) {
        explanation <- suffix_explanations[[suffix]]
        label <- paste(
          "PA variable:",
          ifelse(prefix == "B4WA", "active period,",
            ifelse(prefix == "B4WR", "rest period,",
              "sleep period,"
            )
          ),
          "daily", explanation
        )
        data <- data %>%
          mutate(!!sym(var_name) := datawizard::assign_labels(
            .data[[var_name]],
            variable = label
          ))
      }
    }
  }
  data
}

# List of prefixes
prefixes <- c("B4WA", "B4WR", "B4WS")

# Apply the function to the dataset
data_PA <- assign_variable_labels(data_PA, prefixes, suffix_explanations)

CB_all <- CB_add_OG(CB_all, data_PA, (data_PA %>% select(starts_with("B4WA"), starts_with("B4WS"), starts_with("B4WR")) %>% colnames()), vlabel = TRUE)
data_PA <- reapply_attr2(CB_all, data_PA)

calculate_frequency

function (data, var_name, order_results) 
{
    var <- data[[var_name]]
    freq_table <- data.frame(freq(var, headings = TRUE, order = order_results))
    freq_table <- round(freq_table, 2)
    colnames(freq_table) <- c("Freq", "% Valid", "% Valid Cumul.", 
        "% Total", "% Total Cumul.")
    return(freq_table)
}

CB_add_OG

function (CB_df, data_df, var_names, vclass = TRUE, vlabel = TRUE, 
    val_label = TRUE, vlevel = TRUE, vcomm = TRUE) 
{
    stopifnot(is.data.frame(CB_df), is.data.frame(data_df), is.character(var_names))
    stopifnot(is.logical(vclass), is.logical(vlabel), is.logical(val_label), 
        is.logical(vlevel), is.logical(vcomm))
    for (var_name in var_names) {
        if (!(var_name %in% CB_df[, "Variable_Name"])) {
            new_row <- data.frame(Variable_Name = var_name, OG_Variable_Name = NA, 
                Variable_Class = class(data_df[[var_name]]), 
                Variable_Label = ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "label")), NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label")), 
                Value_Labels = ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "labels")), NA, labels_to_string(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "labels"))), Variable_Levels = ifelse(is.factor(data_df[[var_name]]), 
                  paste(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "levels"), 
                    collapse = ", "), NA), Comments = ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment")), NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment")))
            CB_df <- rbind(CB_df, new_row)
        }
        else if (var_name %in% CB_df[, "Variable_Name"]) {
            if (vclass == TRUE) {
                CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, "Variable_Class"] <- class(data_df[[var_name]])
            }
            if (vlabel == TRUE) {
                CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, "Variable_Label"] <- case_when(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "label")) & is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                  var_name, "Variable_Label"]) ~ NA_character_, 
                  is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label")) & 
                    !is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, 
                      "Variable_Label"]) ~ CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                    var_name, "Variable_Label"], !is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                    "label")) ~ safe_attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                    "label"), TRUE ~ "CHECK")
            }
            if (val_label == TRUE) {
                CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, "Value_Labels"] <- case_when(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "labels")) & is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                  var_name, "Value_Labels"]) ~ NA_character_, 
                  is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "labels")) & 
                    !is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, 
                      "Value_Labels"]) ~ CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                    var_name, "Value_Labels"], !is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                    "labels")) ~ labels_to_string(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                    "labels")), TRUE ~ "CHECK")
            }
            if (vlevel == TRUE) {
                CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, "Variable_Levels"] <- ifelse(is.factor(data_df[[var_name]]), 
                  paste(paste(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "levels"), 
                    sep = ""), collapse = ", "), NA_character_)
            }
            if (vcomm == TRUE) {
                CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == var_name, "Comments"] <- case_when(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment")) & is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                  var_name, "Comments"]) ~ NA_character_, is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment")) & !is.na(CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                  var_name, "Comments"]) ~ CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == 
                  var_name, "Comments"], !is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment")) ~ safe_attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
                  "comment"), TRUE ~ "CHECK")
            }
        }
    }
    return(CB_df)
}

CB_intermediate

function (CB_df, data_df, var_name) 
{
    class_name <- class(data_df[[var_name]])
    desc <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label")), 
        NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label"))
    labels <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "labels")), 
        NA, labels_to_string(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "labels")))
    levels <- ifelse(is.factor(data_df[[var_name]]), paste(paste(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
        "levels"), sep = ""), collapse = ", "), NA)
    comments <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "comment")), 
        NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], "comment"))
    df3 <- data.frame(c(class_name, desc, labels, levels, comments))
    colnames(df3) <- var_name
    CB_df <- CB_df %>% mutate(`:=`(!!var_name, df3[[var_name]]))
    return(CB_df)
}

CB_intermediate2

function (CB_df, data_df, var_names) 
{
    for (var_name in var_names) {
        class_name <- class(data_df[[var_name]])
        desc <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label")), 
            NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], "label"))
        labels <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "labels")), 
            NA, labels_to_string(attr(data_df[[var_name]], "labels")))
        levels <- ifelse(is.factor(data_df[[var_name]]), paste(paste(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
            "levels"), sep = ""), collapse = ", "), NA)
        comments <- ifelse(is.null(attr(data_df[[var_name]], 
            "comment")), NA, attr(data_df[[var_name]], "comment"))
        df3 <- data.frame(c(class_name, desc, labels, levels, 
            comments))
        colnames(df3) <- var_name
        CB_df[[var_name]] <- df3[[var_name]]
    }
    return(CB_df)
}

CB_OG_rename

function (CB_df = CB_df, var_pairs_df = variable_pairs_df) 
{
    for (i in 1:nrow(var_pairs_df)) {
        old_var_name <- var_pairs_df[["OG_Variable_Name"]][i]
        new_var_name <- var_pairs_df[["Variable_Name"]][i]
        if (old_var_name %in% CB_df[, "Variable_Name"]) {
            CB_df[CB_df$Variable_Name == old_var_name, "Variable_Name"] <- new_var_name
        }
    }
    return(CB_df)
}

describe_ND

function (data, vars) 
{
    vars_sym <- rlang::syms(vars)
    describe_var <- function(var_sym) {
        var_data <- data %>% pull(!!var_sym)
        var_name <- as.character(rlang::as_name(var_sym))
        description <- psych::describe(var_data, na.rm = TRUE) %>% 
            round(2) %>% data.frame(., row.names = var_name) %>% 
            select(n, mean, median, sd, min, max, skew, kurtosis, 
                everything(), -vars)
        return(description)
    }
    results <- lapply(vars_sym, describe_var)
    do.call(rbind, results)
}

easy_col_rename

function (select_df_prefix, col_omit) 
{
    df_names <- ls(pattern = select_df_prefix, envir = .GlobalEnv)
    df_names <- df_names[sapply(mget(df_names, envir = .GlobalEnv), 
        is.data.frame)]
    list_of_dfs <- mget(df_names, envir = .GlobalEnv)
    for (df_name in names(list_of_dfs)) {
        df <- list_of_dfs[[df_name]]
        prefix <- gsub("^(.*_).*", "\\1", df_name)
        names(df) <- ifelse(names(df) != col_omit, paste0(prefix, 
            names(df)), names(df))
        list_of_dfs[[df_name]] <- df
    }
    return(list_of_dfs)
}

easy_col_rename_alt

function (select_df_prefix, col_omit) 
{
    df_names <- ls(pattern = select_df_prefix, envir = .GlobalEnv)
    df_names <- df_names[sapply(mget(df_names, envir = .GlobalEnv), 
        is.data.frame)]

    for (df_name in names(list_of_dfs)) {

        list_of_dfs[[df_name]] <- df
    }
    return(list_of_dfs)
}

extract_attributes

function (df) 
{
    var_names <- names(df)
    var_labels <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    var_class <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    var_levels <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    value_labels <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    var_format_SPSS <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    var_format_SAS <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    var_display_width <- vector("list", length(var_names))
    for (i in seq_along(var_names)) {
        var_name <- var_names[i]
        var <- tryCatch(df[[var_name]], error = function(e) NULL)
        if (!is.null(var)) {
            var_labels[[i]] <- ifelse(is.null(attr(var, "label")), 
                NA, attr(var, "label"))
            var_class[[i]] <- ifelse(is.null(class(var)), NA, 
                class(var))
            value_labels[[i]] <- labels_to_string(attr(var, "labels"))
            var_format_SPSS[[i]] <- ifelse(is.null(attr(var, 
                "format.spss")), NA, attr(var, "format.spss"))
            var_format_SAS[[i]] <- ifelse(is.null(attr(var, "format.sas")), 
                NA, attr(var, "format.sas"))
            var_display_width[[i]] <- ifelse(is.null(attr(var, 
                "display_width")), NA, attr(var, "display_width"))
            if (is.factor(var)) {
                var_levels[[i]] <- paste(paste(attr(var, "levels"), 
                  sep = ""), collapse = ", ")
            }
            else {
                var_levels[[i]] <- NA
            }
        }
        else {
            var_labels[[i]] <- NA
            var_class[[i]] <- NA
            value_labels[[i]] <- NA
            var_format_SPSS[[i]] <- NA
            var_format_SAS[[i]] <- NA
            var_display_width[[i]] <- NA
            var_levels[[i]] <- NA
        }
    }
    attributes_list <- list(Variable_Name = var_names, Variable_Class = unlist(var_class), 
        Variable_Label = unlist(var_labels), Variable_Levels = unlist(var_levels, 
            recursive = FALSE), Value_Labels = unlist(value_labels), 
        Variable_Format_SAS = unlist(var_format_SAS), Variable_Format_SPSS = unlist(var_format_SPSS), 
        Variable_displaywidth = unlist(var_display_width))
    attributes_list <- attributes_list[!sapply(attributes_list, 
        is.null)]
    attributes_df <- data.frame(attributes_list)
    return(attributes_df)
}

extract_function_names

function (file_paths) 
{
    file_paths %>% map(read_lines) %>% map(~.x[!str_starts(.x, 
        "#")]) %>% map(str_extract_all, pattern = "\\b\\w+\\s*<-\\s*function") %>%

        unique()
}

extract_function_names2

function (file_paths) 
{
    potential_function_names <- file_paths %>% map(read_lines) %>% 
        map(~.x[!str_starts(.x, "#")]) %>% map(str_extract_all, 
        pattern = "\\b\\w+\\s*<-\\s*function") %>% unlist() %>% 
        map_chr(~str_extract(.x, "\\w+(?=\\s*<-\\s*function)")) %>% 
        unique()
    existing_function_names <- potential_function_names[unlist(lapply(potential_function_names, 
        function(name) {
            exists(name, where = .GlobalEnv)
        }))]
    return(existing_function_names)
}

extract_original_var_names

function (rename_code) 
{
    matches <- regmatches(rename_code, gregexpr("(?<=\\=)\\s*[a-zA-Z0-9_]+", 
        rename_code, perl = TRUE))
    unique_var_names <- unique(unlist(matches))
    trimmed_var_names <- trimws(unique_var_names)
    return(trimmed_var_names)
}

extract_variable_names

function (code_text) 
{
    pattern <- "\\b([[:alnum:]_]+)\\s*=\\s*(datawizard::assign_labels\\(|sjlabelled::set_labels\\(|sjlabelled::as_label\\(|as\\.numeric\\(|as\\.character\\(|assign_labels\\(|set_labels\\(|as_label\\()"
    matches <- gregexpr(pattern, code_text, perl = TRUE)
    variable_names <- regmatches(code_text, matches)
    variable_names <- lapply(variable_names, function(x) gsub(pattern, 
        "\\1", x))
    variable_names <- unlist(variable_names)
    variable_names <- variable_names[variable_names != ""]
    unique(variable_names)
}

extract_variable_pairs

function (text = text) 
{
    original_vars <- regmatches(text, gregexpr("(?<=\\=)\\s*[a-zA-Z0-9_]+", 
        text, perl = TRUE))
    original_vars <- unique(unlist(original_vars))
    original_vars <- trimws(original_vars)
    new_vars <- regmatches(text, gregexpr("\\b[a-zA-Z0-9_]+(?=\\s*=)", 
        text, perl = TRUE))
    new_vars <- unique(unlist(new_vars))
    new_vars <- trimws(new_vars)
    variable_pairs <- data.frame(OG_Variable_Name = original_vars, 
        Variable_Name = new_vars)
    return(variable_pairs)
}

generate_label_code

function (data_name, compare_data_name) 
{
    if (!exists(data_name) || !exists(compare_data_name)) {
        stop("One or both datasets not found in the global environment")
    }
    unique_vars <- setdiff(names(get(data_name)), names(get(compare_data_name)))
    output_code <- paste0(data_name, " <- ", data_name, " %>%", 
        "\n  mutate(")
    for (var in unique_vars) {
        output_code <- paste0(output_code, "\n    ", var, " = datawizard::assign_labels(", 
            "\n      ", var, ",", "\n      variable = \"\"", 
            "\n      ),")
    }
    output_code <- substr(output_code, 1, nchar(output_code) - 
        1)
    output_code <- paste0(output_code, "\n  )")
    cat(output_code, "\n")
}

generate_labels

function (dataset) 
{
    dataset_name <- ensym(dataset)
    if (!is.data.frame(get(dataset))) {
        stop("Input must be a data frame.")
    }
    colNames <- names(get(dataset))
    syntaxString <- paste0(dataset, " <- ", dataset, " %>% \n  ungroup() %>% \n  mutate(\n")
    for (colName in colNames) {
        syntaxString <- paste0(syntaxString, "    ", colName, 
            " = labelled(\n      ", colName, ",\n      labels = NULL,\n      label = NULL\n),\n")
    }
    syntaxString <- substr(syntaxString, 1, nchar(syntaxString) - 
        2)
    syntaxString <- paste0(syntaxString, "\n  )")
    cat(syntaxString)
}

ggplot_hist_with_curve_ggplot

function (data, var_name, i) 
{
    df <- data.frame(x = data[[var_name]])
    mu <- mean(df$x, na.rm = TRUE)
    sigma <- sd(df$x, na.rm = TRUE)
    p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x)) + geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(density)), 
        bins = 30, fill = "white", color = "black", alpha = 1) + 
        stat_function(fun = dnorm, args = list(mean = mu, sd = sigma), 
            col = "#b28a8c", lwd = 1) + ND_ggplot_theme + labs(title = (paste("Histogram of", 
        var_name, i)), x = (paste(var_name)))
}

ggplot_hist_with_curve_ggplot_WT

function (data, var_name, vline, unit, line_label, i, line_color = "red") 
{
    df <- data.frame(x = data[[var_name]])
    mu <- mean(df$x, na.rm = TRUE)
    sigma <- sd(df$x, na.rm = TRUE)
    density_data <- density(df$x, na.rm = TRUE)
    max_density <- max(density_data$y)
    p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x)) + geom_histogram(aes(y = after_stat(density)), 
        bins = 30, fill = "white", color = "black", alpha = 1) + 
        stat_function(fun = dnorm, args = list(mean = mu, sd = sigma), 
            col = "#b28a8c", lwd = 1) + geom_vline(xintercept = vline, 
        color = line_color, linetype = "dashed", linewidth = 1) + 
        annotate("text", x = vline + (0.05 * vline), y = max_density - 
            (0.05 * max_density), label = line_label, size = 3, 
            angle = 90, hjust = 0, vjust = 1) + labs(title = paste("Histogram of", 
        var_name, i), x = paste0("WT in ", unit)) + bargraph_theme
    return(p)
}

labels_to_string

function (named_vector) 
{
    if (is.null(named_vector)) {
        return(NA)
    }
    pairs <- paste(named_vector, names(named_vector), sep = " = ")
    return(paste(pairs, collapse = ", "))
}

load_rds

function (rds_file, overwrite = FALSE, rename_conflict = TRUE) 
{
    obj_name <- sub("^.*((data_|CB_).*)\\.rds$", "\\1", basename(rds_file))
    obj_name <- gsub("[- ]", "_", obj_name)
    if (exists(obj_name, envir = .GlobalEnv)) {
        if (overwrite) {
            message(paste("Overwriting existing object:", obj_name))
        }
        else if (rename_conflict) {
            original_name <- obj_name
            counter <- 1
            while (exists(obj_name, envir = .GlobalEnv)) {
                obj_name <- paste0(original_name, "_", counter)
            }
            message(paste("Renaming loaded object to:", obj_name))
        }
        else {
            stop("Object name exists. Set overwrite = TRUE to overwrite or rename_conflict = TRUE to rename.")
        }
    }
    assign(obj_name, readRDS(rds_file), envir = .GlobalEnv)
}

plot_bar_graph_multi

function (data, var_name) 
{
    data2 <- na.omit(data[, var_name, drop = FALSE])
    data2[[var_name]] <- factor(data2[[var_name]])

    max_x <- length(data2[[var_name]])
    min_x <- length(data2[[var_name]])
    p <- ggplot(data2, aes(x = !!sym(var_name))) + geom_bar(fill = "grey80", 
        alpha = 0.7, color = "black") + ND_ggplot_theme + labs(title = (paste("Bargraph of", 
        var_name)), y = "Count", x = (paste(var_name))) + geom_segment(aes(x = 0.3,

}

reactable_freq_data

function (df, var_names) 
{
    results_list <- list()
    for (var_name in var_names) {
        freq_df <- as.data.frame(summarytools::freq(df %>% select({
            {
                var_name
            }
        }), report.nas = TRUE, headings = TRUE, round.digits = 2))
        colnames(freq_df) <- c("Freq", "Perc_Valid", "PV_Cumul", 
            "Perc_Total", "PT_Cumul")
        results_list[[var_name]] <- freq_df
    }
    return(results_list)
}

reapply_attr

function (CB_df, data_df) 
{
    variable_labels <- CB_df["Variable_Label", ]
    value_labels <- CB_df["Value_Labels", ]
    comments <- CB_df["Comments", ]
    for (var in names(data_df)) {
        if (var %in% names(variable_labels)) {
            if (!is.na(CB_df["Variable_Label", var])) {
                attr(data_df[[var]], "label") <- as.character(variable_labels[var])
            }
            if (!is.na(CB_df["Value_Labels_Code", var])) {
                pairs <- unlist(strsplit(as.character(value_labels[var]), 
                  ", "))
                names <- c()
                values <- c()
                for (pair in pairs) {
                  elements <- strsplit(pair, " = ")[[1]]
                  name <- elements[2]
                  value <- as.numeric(elements[1])
                  names <- c(names, name)
                  values <- c(values, value)
                }
                attr(data_df[[var]], "labels") <- values
                names(attr(data_df[[var]], "labels")) <- names
            }
            if (!is.na(CB_df["Comments", var])) {
                comment(data_df[[var]]) <- as.character(comments[var])
            }
        }
    }
    return(data_df)
}

reapply_attr2

function (CB_df, data_df) 
{
    variable_labels <- CB_df %>% dplyr::select(Variable_Name, 
        Variable_Label) %>% dplyr::filter(!is.na(Variable_Label))
    value_labels <- CB_df %>% dplyr::select(Variable_Name, Value_Labels) %>% 
        dplyr::filter(!is.na(Value_Labels))
    comments <- CB_df %>% dplyr::select(Variable_Name, Comments) %>% 
        dplyr::filter(!is.na(Comments))
    for (var in names(data_df)) {
        if (var %in% variable_labels[, "Variable_Name"]) {
            attr(data_df[[var]], "label") <- as.character(variable_labels[variable_labels$Variable_Name == 
                var, "Variable_Label"])
        }
        if (var %in% value_labels[, "Variable_Name"]) {
            pairs <- unlist(strsplit(as.character(value_labels[value_labels$Variable_Name == 
                var, "Value_Labels"]), ","))
            names <- c()
            values <- c()
            for (pair in pairs) {
                elements <- strsplit(pair, "=")[[1]]
                name <- trimws(elements[2])
                value <- trimws(elements[1])
                names <- c(names, name)
                values <- c(values, value)
            }
            attr(data_df[[var]], "labels") <- values
            names(attr(data_df[[var]], "labels")) <- names
        }
        if (var %in% comments[, "Variable_Name"]) {
            comment(data_df[[var]]) <- as.character(comments[comments$Variable_Name == 
                var, "Comments"])
        }
    }
    return(data_df)
}

    })

render_toc3

function (filename, toc_header_name = "Table of Contents", base_level = NULL, 
    toc_depth = 3) 
{
    x <- readLines(filename, warn = FALSE)
    x <- paste(x, collapse = "\n")
    x <- paste0("\n", x, "\n")
    for (i in 5:3) {
        regex_code_fence <- paste0("\n[`]{", i, "}.+?[`]{", i, 
            "}\n")
        x <- gsub(regex_code_fence, "\n\n", x)
    }
    x <- strsplit(x, "\n")[[1]]
    x <- x[grepl("^#+", x)]
    if (!is.null(toc_header_name)) 
        x <- x[!grepl(paste0("^#+ ", toc_header_name), x)]
    if (is.null(base_level)) 
        base_level <- min(sapply(gsub("(#+).+", "\\1", x), nchar))
    start_at_base_level <- FALSE
    unique_id <- 0
    last_level <- NULL
    level <- NULL
    result <- character(0)
    count <- 0
    for (i in seq_along(x)) {
        h <- x[i]
        last_level <- level
        level <- nchar(gsub("(#+).+", "\\1", h)) - base_level
        h <- gsub("`r", "{{", h)
        h <- gsub("` ", "}} ", h)
        h <- knitr::knit_expand(text = h, delim = c("{{", "}}"))
        if (level < 0) {
            stop("Cannot have negative header levels. Problematic header \"", 
                h, "\" ", "was considered level ", level, ". Please adjust `base_level`.")
        }
        if (level > toc_depth - 1) {
            next
        }
        if (!start_at_base_level && level == 0) {
            start_at_base_level <- TRUE
        }
        if (!start_at_base_level) {
            next
        }
        if (grepl("\\{.*\\.unlisted.*\\}", h)) {
            next
        }
        if (grepl("^#+.*\\{[^}]*#.*\\}", h)) {
            header_text <- gsub("^#+ (.+)\\s+?\\{.+$", "\\1", 
                h)
            header_text <- trimws(header_text)
            header_slug <- gsub("^#+.*\\{[^#]*#([^ }]+).*\\}.*", 
                "\\1", h)
        }
        else {
            h <- gsub("^#+\\s+?", "", h)
            header_text <- gsub("\\{.*?\\}", "", h)
            header_text <- trimws(header_text)
            header_slug <- paste(strsplit(header_text, " ")[[1]], 
                collapse = "-")
            header_slug <- tolower(header_slug)
        }
        if (nchar(header_text) == 0) {
            next
        }
        count <- count + 1
        if (level == 0) {
            unique_id <- unique_id + 1
            collapsible_id <- paste0("collapse-", unique_id)
            c <- ""
            if (count == 1) {
                c <- paste0("\n\n<span class=\"toc\"><ul>\n", 
                  c)
            }
            if (count != 1) {
                c <- paste0("</div>\n</div>\n")
            }
            c <- paste0(c, paste0("<li>", " <a href=\"#", header_slug, 
                "\">", header_text, " </a>", "<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-light\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#", 
                collapsible_id, "\" aria-expanded=\"true\" aria-controls=\"", 
                collapsible_id, "\">", "<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" fill=\"currentColor\" class=\"bi bi-chevron-down\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\">\n  <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M1.646 4.646a.5.5 0 0 1 .708 0L8 10.293l5.646-5.647a.5.5 0 0 1 .708.708l-6 6a.5.5 0 0 1-.708 0l-6-6a.5.5 0 0 1 0-.708z\"/>\n</svg></button> </li> </br>"), 
                "\n", "<div class=\"collapse show\" id=\"", collapsible_id, 
                "\">\n", "<div class=\"ps-4 mt-2\">", "\n\n")
            result <- c(result, c)
        }
        else {
            d <- ""
            count <- count + 1
            d <- paste0("<li>", " <a href=\"#", header_slug, 
                "\">", header_text, "</a> </li></br>\n")
            if (last_level < level) {
                d <- paste0("\n<ul>\n", d)
            }
            if (last_level > level) {
                d <- paste0("\n</ul>\n", d)
            }
            result <- c(result, d)
        }
    }
    length <- as.numeric(length(result))
    result[[length]] <- paste0(result[[length]], "\n</ul>\n</span>\n")
    knitr::asis_output(paste(result, collapse = "\n"))
}

save_data

function (obj_name) 
{
    obj <- get(obj_name, envir = .GlobalEnv)
    if (is.data.frame(obj) || is.matrix(obj)) {
        file_name <- xfun::sans_ext(basename(rstudioapi::getActiveDocumentContext()$path))
        file_name <- gsub("[- ]", "_", file_name)
        write.csv(obj, file = paste0("./cache/", file_name, "_", 
            obj_name, ".csv"), row.names = FALSE)
    }
    else {
        stop("Object is not a dataframe or matrix and cannot be saved as a CSV file.")
    }
}
